    "content": "nullEinstein Personalization\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Einstein Personalization\n Einstein Personalization\n Einstein Personalization and Data Cloud Setup\n Creating and Training Einstein Personalization Recommenders\n Choosing a Recommendation Type\n Configure a Recommender\n Configure Recommendation Filters\n Track Personalization Recommender Training Status\n Personalization Points\n Personalization Analytics\n Einstein Personalization References\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nEINSTEIN PERSONALIZATION\nCreating and Training Einstein Personalization Recommenders\n\nBuilt on Salesforce Data Cloud, personalized recommendations use deep, digital, and offline behavioral and business context data to provide multichannel, focused, individualized recommendations. To create personalized recommendations, you configure a recommender and train it using Data Cloud data graphs that you select.\n\nChoosing a Recommendation Type\nWhen configuring a recommender, you can choose between two recommendation types—goal-based recommendations or rule-based recommendations.\nConfigure a Recommender\nYou configure recommenders to present personalized recommendations to visitors. Recommenders use Data Cloud data graphs to identify who is eligible to receive personalized content, and what content is available to recommend. The recommender also uses a selected goal or insight rules to determine the type of recommendation you want to present. Recommenders can return up to 12 recommendations at a time for each personalization point.\nConfigure Recommendation Filters\nDefine optional recommendation filters to either include or exclude eligible content that matches filter conditions.\nTrack Personalization Recommender Training Status\nImmediately after you create a personalization recommender, it uses Customer 360 data from the selected Data Cloud data graphs to begin training. You can track training and refresh status for each recommender on its individual record.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
